HEADWORD: mahon stock
<hw>ma*hon" stock`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An annual
cruciferous plant with reddish purple or white flowers (<spn>Malcolmia
maritima</spn>). It is called in England <altname>Virginia
stock</altname>, but the plant comes from the Mediterranean.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mahoohoo</ent>⟦br⟧
